<user_id>106354209588970807404</user_id><Name>Dustin J.<//Name>< Time>
1570832524956</Time>
< Rate>
5</Rate>
< text>
I went here and ordered the Pho Dac Biet. They only have one size bowl, so I got extra noodles because I was really hungry.

I got my food really quickly and was pleased with the amount of beef they threw in there.

Unfortunately, an emergency occurred and I had to step away for a considerable time. When I came back, the server had already taken my barely eaten first bowl, started a brand new bowl, and brought it to me piping hot. I thought this was customer service at it's best. They could have left me with a cold bowl of soup, but they cared enough to make sure I enjoyed their food.

The steak was cooked well and one type was fairly thick. I can't say I've ever seen  steak this thick before in Pho Dac Biet, but it was tender and fell apart at the touch of my chop sticks.

Ultimately, I really enjoyed this meal and the excellent service the server provided to me. I'm going to come back here again for sure.< /text>

<userid>117707312859038144979<//userid>< name>
Maximilian J. Cao<//name>
< Time>
1508438690584< /Time>
<rating>5< /rating><Review>Love their bun bo hue and pho. Flavors are on poont amd very authentic and traditional when it comes to their fresh flat noodles. They have friendly staff as well.</Review><Pics>None< /Pics><response>{'time': 1515655052715, 'text': 'Thanks'}< /response><gmap_id>0x80900d626f733577:0x67b68031fed54d2d</gmap_id></record>
</dataset><record>
< Text>
Ate here for the first time Saturday 10/21/2017.  It was a fantastic experience.

Firstly, it was a Saturday around midday so there weren't too many patrons inside.  Please don't let the adjoined building ward you off!  When you walk in you're greeted to a personal atmosphere that has room for 19 with space enough to be comfortable.

I ordered the E1 pho, which came with thinly sliced beef, pork nuggets, tripe, and a generous helping of two large pieces of tendon, on top of the traditional onion, chive, cilantro, etc.  Thai Basil, bean sprouts, jalapeno slices, and lime served on the side to add to your liking, as well as Hoisin, Sriracha and a variety of other sauces.

Each of the meats, were cooked very well.  The beef was extremely tender, the pork was flavorful and not gamey, the tripe was clean with no grit whatsoever.  The broth it came in was fantastic.  It was spiced well, an even mix of flavors that complemented the mix of vegetables and meats within.  Personally, I only placed a few leaves of Thai Basil, and dumped quite a bit of sprouts in.

One thing I did want to draw attention to on it's own was the pieces of tendon within the bowl.  Often times, it's easy to cook tendon and be done with it, the results still being slightly chewy...this was not the case.  The tendon was cooked throughout to practically fall apart, but it was easily able to be handled into the mouth with chopsticks and simply melt from there.

The noodles had good flavor, with a good portion size proportionate to the very generous serving of the pho itself.

To note, I tasted the broth, meats, vegetables, BEFORE adding only about a Tbsp of Sriracha.

Fountain drinks are offered.

Don't let the location or the adjoining building scare you off from enjoying this gem hidden in downtown Stockton!< /Text>

< Text>
First time coming here, ordered 4 pupusas to-go, each with a different filling. I ordered in Spanish because I speak it but they had a bilingual menu. I waited about 12-15 minutes and my order was ready. Being my first time here didn't realize the pupusas are actually made to order! They came out hot, with coleslaw and sauce on the side. I went home and ate them, sooo good! Super delicious. Will be coming back again.

UPDATE: Have been coming here for over a year, and the quality of the pupusas is consistently DELICIOUS. Thank you!</Text>

<rating>5< /rating><Review>This pupuseria is tucked away behind other businesses; if you are not a local, you may miss it.  Do not miss it.  The food is unfailingly fresh, the menu diverse and the cheese in the papusas is all warm and melty.  They make the pupusas to order, so either call ahead or be ready to kick back in this casual eatery.

I had the shrimp papusa and the mushroom papusa and both filled me up, for sure. There are so many varieties of papusas on the menu; they even make spinach papusas.  The menu includes other Salvadorean food and Mexican food as well.  The staff are welcoming and seem to enjoy their jobs!  Oh.  They also have pastries!< /Review>< Pictures>

< userid>
101761160258249878813<//userid>
<Name>Il Hwan Lee<//Name><time>1573365455790< /time><Rate>2<//Rate>< review>
I'm not sure why others are so generous with the review on this place. I had the sashimi, roll, tempura, katsu, specials and etc and I can say that the most fundamental basics were off from the beginning. For example, soy sauce is not the right kind you should be using for sushi and has strong salty taste without the flavor of soy at the end, wasabi was bland and hardly had the kick, miso soup was diluted and sugary. Even if it's a budget sushi place I didn't feel that I was getting good bang for the buck. I would say this place is on par with qaulity of mall food court sushi but the condiments on the side worsens the experience and ginger isn't strong enough to reset the taste buds. Just having the basics right would bring the quality up a bit if they cared.</review>

<rate>5</rate><Pics>None</Pics><date>1419620078550</date>< text>
Randomly came upon Arashi Sushi House on Chrsitmas Day as we were desperately trying to find something opened without a long wait. LUCKY US! Stepping into the clean, soft lighting of the newly painted and tastefully simple decor done with a touch of class drew us in for more. The service was great as they were kind and patient with us spending an enormous amount of time trying to decide bringing edamame on the house as we scanned the menu.  Presentation was lovely as expected with Japanese dishes. Between the three of us we decided on Tempura Udon, Chicken Udon, Unagi Don and a "White Out" sushi roll that was ladened with Hamachi and Walu! Would definetly order the same again when we return (not IF!) We were told they have only been opened for 2 months which would explain the "street view" photo. Don't let outside appearances fool you. The prices were also a nice surprise. There are sports TV screens high above on the walls to satisfy those that may need a break from conversation!<//text>

<username>Kath leen< /username>< Date>
1429666336072</Date>
< Rating>
3< /Rating>
<Review>Bye Bye Rockin' Crawfish
Hi Arashi Sushi House

Arashi Sushi House took over the location of where Rockin' Crawfish use to be. Like many sushi restaurants in the Richmond district, this is another addition to the neighborhood.

Arashi has an extensive menu. Lunch specials. Cold and hot appetizers. Salad. Sushi rolls. Entrees and even ramen! Dessert and sake. Happy Hour - Monday thru Friday 5pm-8pm.

Hamachi Kama (yellowtail collar) was delicious and perfectly cooked. The sashimi was simply fresh. The rice on the sushi rolls were a bit too soft and soggy.

The Whole Fish Sashimi (Black Sea Bream) was the best of it all! The fish was cut thinly and beautifully presented and plated. The fish not only looked picture worthy, but tasted fresh too! It came with fresh wasabi and 3 dipping sauces. I didn't know that fresh wasabi didn't taste as spicy as regular wasabi.

The service was superb! Our waters and tea was refilled constantly. Since we ordered a lot of dishes, they were nice enough to move the small table next to us to combine it into one long table so we would have more space.

I'll be back to try the other items on their menu!< /Review><pics>None<//pics>< Resp>
None< /Resp>

<user_id>115490016874816273199<//user_id>< Name>
Hannah< /Name>
< time>
1564286688155</time>
<Rate>5< /Rate>< text>
I love Vampire Penguin. Being from Utah, our family had no idea what to expect. For all we knew it was just a snow cone. Boy were we wrong! It is such a unique texture and was definitely worth our time. They have unique flavors such as s'moreos and Tuxedo. It is like a cold cake with cool flavors and textures. This place is worth your time.< /text>

< userid>
105700469028059022332< /userid>
< text>
Saw the big ad while headed south bound on the 101 and immediately had to pull over... LOVE Vampire Penguin!! I've been to the Sacramento location and this one is much bigger with friendly vibes inside. Shaved snow is a trendy dessert that is great year round... it's also an Instagramable alternative to ice cream and doesn't leave you in a food coma.

We did a build your own with half Thai tea, half coffee snow topped with Oreos and condensed milk. The Oreos are just the perfect pop of texture with the snow. Large is the right size for 2 to share, it's worth the few extra dollars more.

If you're driving through Eureka and craving something sweet, definitely hit this place up!<//text>

So, my husband and I both ordered a chicken super burrito. I honestly thought it was going to be good when the cashier let me know what was inside but I was so wrong. The burrito was a very big flour tortilla, it was filled with too much onion, Pico de Gallo, guacamole and lettuce. It has a little bit of rice, a little bit of sour cream a little bit of beans and hardly any chicken. The sauce on top was cold and it was so gross. I had eaten here before and the wet burrito was good but I don't know if they changed owner or what but now it's nasty. And to top it off we paid 9.50 per burrito and it wasn't even worth it. <rate>5< /rate><review>American made products and locally run by real people who care. I was looking to get a punching bag for my home and wanted to support a small business and find something that was Made in the USA, I came across the FIGHT SHOP online and was pleased with the selection of american made PROLAST items and decided to purchase a heavy bag and a set of puzzle mats. Unfortunately in my zeal to order I didn't realize I had ordered a youth-size bag instead of an adult one. But, never fear, Dan noticed this and called me to confirm and after discussing what I needed/wanted adjusted my order to ensure I got exactly what I needed. None of these massive online retailers can offer that kind of service, I can't express how delighted I am I chose to go this route as I would have been incredibly disappointed to not find this out until it showed up at my house. It was worth the price, including the shipping as it had to be sent cross-country via frieght. I highly recommend the FIGHT SHOP to anyone in the market for training, MMA, boxing gear--high quality product and high quality customer service. Thanks Dan and the rest of the team! < Text>
Till date I have not found a truthful HVAC Company.  This company gets two stars because they are one star better than the worst conman I had dealt with before this when the capacitor had failed.

Their technician showed up promptly with mask and booties.  Did some fake tricks, appeared scared and genuinely concerned.  Thanks to Hollywood, I know some acting too and can read body language, but this guy was good, he looked me in the eye while lying, but something else gave it away! (Spoiler alert - not good acting)

He showed me a couple of photos of rust in the drain pan, two sheet metal screws that had distorted the holes (either by him or someone from his company who had come a few months ago, pre-covid), some removed bolts on the attic floor.  Hmm he spent an hour in the attic, the bolts must have just fallen off with his stare.  These were some insignificant metal sheets he was pointing to with distorted holes.  He then said the whole equipment has to be replaced as everything is rusted and the gas furnace is spilling gas into the attic space.  This conman quoted me $6000+ for a new furnace, another $8000 for compressor system that will work in conjunction with the rated BTU.  While the previous company who had not even looked at the furnace had said $18000+ for compressor system and $30000 for brand new everything.

All that because some $30 worth of 1/4" rubber hoses and condensation pipes has to be replaced and he is neither skilled nor qualified to do that.  From what I noticed, he had disabled all the safety switches, tampered with kill switch in the furnace panel door, dismantled the gas cutoff switch and let it dangle close the the burner (showed a pic and said someone had done it on purpose), turned off gas and power supply lines, disconnected the electrical wires.  He said he did all that 'to prevent my house from catching fire and saved our family from a catastrophe.'

Boy! I was scared to see the rust and the furnace burner firing up from his video.< /Text>
